How To Run The Unit Test With Mantis On Your Machine In a Console
====================================

1. Bulid the whole calendar project with bld.
	sn.widget.cal\lwp>bld

2. Change the directory to 'build\unittest'.
	sn.widget.cal\lwp>cd build\unittest

3. Copy the files ('db.properties' and 'db.template.properties') from 'properties\src' to the unittest directory.
	sn.widgets.cal\lwp\build\calendar.test\unittest>cp properties\src\db.template.properties .
	sn.widgets.cal\lwp\build\calendar.test\unittest>cp properties\src\db.properties .

4. Edit the 'db.properties' file. Enable the raw db properties and disable the jndi.
e.g.
	database.schema=CALENDAR

	database.driver=com.ibm.db2.jcc.DB2Driver
	database.url=jdbc:db2://lcauto61.swg.usma.ibm.com:50000/SNCOMM
	database.user=db2inst1
	database.password=hnivcmpz

	#database.jndi=java:comp/env/jdbc/calendar

NOTE: Using a remote db (like a db on the server pool) will make the unit test very slow.

5. Make a directory with name 'jdbc'.
	sn.widgets.cal\lwp\build\calendar.test\unittest>mkdir jdbc

6. Run the Junit test.
	sn.widgets.cal\lwp\build\calendar.test\unittest>bld -f runtests.xml report

p.s.
One can choose which testcase to run by editing the property 'name' of '//target[@name="test"]/junit/sysproperty/test' in runtests.xml
